  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>linguine</strong> and reserve a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1646.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1646.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1646.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1646.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1646.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the linguine is cooking, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and leave the garlic to infuse the oil</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
